The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a sixth day, dropping 0.7
percent to 20,089.31. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index was little
changed at 2,689.79.  Trevali Mining Corp. (TV)  , a Canadian silver and zinc
producer with operations in Peru, fell 4.3 percent to 88 cents
on investor concern that growth in  China  is slowing, said
Hernando Pastor, an analyst at Lima-based Kallpa Securities SAB.  Sulliden Gold Corp Ltd. (SUE)  , an exploration company,
dropped 2.8 percent to $1.04 as the metal declined for a second
day in  New York .  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peruâ€™s biggest producer of
the metal, gained 1.3 percent to $31.15 as copper advanced in
